# Orchestrator Control Plane

The orchestrator schedules and converges work. It does not own SSOT, RTL, TB, coverage, or EDA artifacts.

Use these references before changing orchestrator behavior:

- `doc/wiki/orchestrator-worker-handoff.md`
- `doc/wiki/orchestrator-loop-on-react-loop-plan.md`
- `doc/wiki/orchestrator-llm-loop-phase3.md`
- `doc/wiki/pipeline-progress-debugging.md`
- `workflow/COMMON_ENGINE_FLOW.md`

Worker-to-worker dispatch is not the control model. A worker may emit evidence, workflow feedback, or `suggested_handoff`; the orchestrator decides whether to dispatch, persist, retry, mark stale, or stop for human review.

Respect session and root isolation. Do not assume one global `ATLAS_*` environment or one global running agent when the UI can operate across workers, sessions, or IP roots.

UI code should render orchestrator state and user decisions. It should not reimplement stage validators or silently patch generated artifacts.
